HEADWORD: Perennibranchiate
<hw>Per*en`ni*bran"chi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Perennial</er>, and <er>Branchiate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having branch⟦ae⟧, or gills, through life; --
said especially of certain Amphibia, like the menobranchus. Opposed to
<contr>caducibranchiate</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Belonging to the
Perennibranchiata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perennity</ent>⟦br⟧
